# Epic and Ticket Population

When creating or updating epics/tickets, complete **both** `context/planning/epics.md` and Notion. Do not leave blank Notion page bodies.

## Epics (`epics.md` + Notion Epics DB)

- **epics.md:** Status, Goal, Roadmap home, Priority guidance (or Hold), full ticket table (ID, Title, Status, Priority, Notes).
- **Notion page body:** Goal, Context links (repo paths), Acceptance for the epic, Out of scope, Child tickets list, Dependencies — see `context/planning/epic-template.md`.
- Mirror Epic ID, Status, Roadmap, Repo notes properties.

## Tickets (`ticket-template.md` + Notion Tickets DB)

- Follow `context/planning/ticket-template.md` on Notion body and `tickets/TICKET-XXXX.md`.
- Required for every `ready` / `active` / `needs-approval` ticket; prefer stubs for all children.
- Mirror Ticket ID, Status, Priority, Agent, Acceptance (short), Repo notes, Epic relation.
- **New tickets:** stub bodies include all template sections from creation (Goal through Agent notes). Do not invent a thinner format.
- **Before `needs-approval` (all new work):** fill **What changed** on both repo stub and Notion — summary, files/surfaces, schema/API deltas, samples, verification evidence, decisions, leftover risk. Review must not depend on chat history. Do not backfill historical `done` tickets unless the owner asks.

## Sync and approval

- Edit `epics.md` first for material Status/Priority/scope; then mirror Notion.
- Agents set Status → `needs-approval` after verification; **never** set `done` (owner only).
- No Notion-only cards as planned work until they appear in `epics.md`.

```text
❌ BAD: Notion epic/ticket with properties only and empty body
❌ BAD: needs-approval with only checked acceptance boxes / vague Agent notes
✅ GOOD: epics.md row + Notion body from epic/ticket template + stub when ready/active
✅ GOOD: needs-approval includes a concrete What changed section
```
